main event: An unidentified flying object was spotted by the crew of the USCGC Bartaria on February 28, 1961.
interesting points: The object's brightness was that of a first magnitude star.
The object was observed at an approximate high altitude, with a bearing of 270 degrees and an angle of 15 degrees.
The object then changed its bearing to 135 degrees and its angle to 5 degrees.
The report concludes that the object was possibly a satellite.
The report was sent as an advance copy to several military commands.
